# Tailwind Styling Rule

- Do not use inline styles (`style=""` in HTML or `style={{}}` in JS/TS).
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for all visual styling.
- If a value is reused or is part of design language (colors, spacing, font sizes, radii), extract it into Tailwind tokens/config first, then use class names.
- Prefer semantic utility usage (`bg-primary`, `text-muted`, `px-6`) over ad-hoc arbitrary values.
- For one-off dynamic behavior, prefer toggling Tailwind classes in JS rather than setting inline style properties.

## Examples

```html
<!-- Bad -->
<div style="width:293px;height:52px;"></div>

<!-- Good -->
<div class="w-[293px] h-[52px]"></div>
```

```js
// Bad
el.style.backgroundColor = '#092137';

// Good
el.classList.add('bg-navy');
```

